The Micron MT29F32G08CBACAWP identifies reliably and returns a valid ONFI
parameter page, but advertises its ECC requirements through a 48-byte
extended parameter page. The NAND core attempts to read it at column 768,
immediately after the three standard parameter-page copies, and the
Berlin2CD probe-only operation filter rejects that column-change command.

Permit only the exact read-only sequence required by this device:
RNDOUT, column 0x0300, RNDOUTSTART and 48 data bytes. Execute it through
the existing NFCv2 length-override PIO path, validate the extended-page
CRC and EPPS signature, and report the ECC section's strength and step
size. Also decode the ONFI endurance exponent instead of printing its two
encoded bytes as a little-endian integer.

The controller remains probe-only. Ordinary page and OOB reads, MTD
registration, DMA, erase and program operations remain unavailable.

